Andrew Gavin Marshall is an independent writer both on the contemporary structures of capitalism as well as on the history of the global political economy. He is a Research Associate with the Centre for Research on Globalization (CRG). 

Born: 6 May 1987 (age 36 years)

Books: THE GLOBAL ECONOMIC CRISIS. The Great Depression of the XXI Century

 
Andrew is Project Manager of [https://thepeoplesbookproject.com/ The People's Book Project], an initiative through which he is attempting to write a comprehensive book on the institutions and ideas of power in our world, and what we can do about it.

